SQL :

It is properly managed and structured.
It stores data in tables, in rows and columns.
Mostly used for banking, complex queries, Erp system such as business, finance, human resource,etc
Famous tools MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracel,etc.


NoSQL:

It is unstructed and raw like random.
It stores data as key value pairs, graphs.
Mostly used for soial media, IoT Data storage, real time processing, big data applications.
Famous tools MongoDB, Couchbase, Azure Comos DB.
